  34,23,"No intercession will be of any benefit with Him, except by those granted permission by Him. ňĻAt last,ňļ when the dread ňĻof Judgment Dayňļ is relieved from their hearts ňĻbecause they are permitted to intercedeňļ, they will ňĻexcitedlyňļ ask ňĻthe angelsňļ, ‚ÄúWhat has your Lord ňĻjustňļ said?‚ÄĚ The angels will reply, ‚ÄúThe truth! And He is the Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  34,24,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho provides for you from the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúAllah! Now, certainly one of our two groups¬†is ňĻrightlyňļ guided; the other is clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
